OL,3,CPub owner says business rates changes
OL,4,Cwill cost him #20,000 more per year
OL,6,FThis means some business owners will
OL,7,Fbe paying a smaller percentage on a
OL,8,Fhigher value - thus, some will pay
OL,9,Fmore than they did previously despite
OL,10,Fthe multiplier decrease.
OL,12,FFor example, a business currently
OL,13,Fpaying 49% of #10,000 might find
OL,14,Fthemselves paying 43% of #20,000 from
OL,15,FApril next year. That's an extra
OL,16,F#3,700 per year.
OL,18,FPhasing out of Covid relief
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
